.TH POHODA-ZABBIX-STATUS 1 "May 2026" "pohoda-zabbix" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
pohoda-zabbix-status \- check Pohoda mServer connectivity for Zabbix
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B pohoda-zabbix-status
[\fB\-\-env\fR=\fIFILE\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Tests connectivity to the Pohoda mServer API. Outputs 1 if connected,
0 if not reachable. Exit code 0 on success, 1 on failure.
.PP
Designed as a Zabbix UserParameter for the
.B pohoda.server.connectivity
item.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-env=\fIFILE\fR
Path to .env configuration file.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B POHODA_URL
Pohoda mServer URL.
.TP
.B POHODA_USERNAME
mServer username.
.TP
.B POHODA_PASSWORD
mServer password.
.TP
.B POHODA_ICO
Company identification number.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR pohoda-zabbix-digest (1),
.BR zabbix_agent2 (8)
.SH AUTHOR
Vítězslav Dvořák <info@vitexsoftware.cz>
